Never disappoints. Fresh Greek food. Authentic and the price is right.

[This review, strangely enough, got moved to the page of the co-business, Avli. I'm reposting it here now.] My time at Avli the Kafe was superb, especially for their opening night: the service was a strong point, I liked my crepe and tea, …
Food is great. Service was prompt and the pleasant. Love the atmosphere. Foti treated us royally :) Mike & Maria
I've been coming here for years, friendly family run restaurant with some of the best Greek offerings.  Grilled octopus and calamari are terrific.

Solid Greek food, good selection, even had a vegetarian moussaka which is rare. Not the very best I ever had and the wait is long on the weekends but decent, good food and excellent, friendly service.
Excellent
Great food and atmosphere. The gyros are the best I've had. The lemon potatoes are the best sides. Great pita to go along with the food.
My local go to restaurant for a guaranteed great meal. Reasonably priced, decent service. Food speaks for itself !! A must if your in the neighborhood (Order anything Lamb and the Lemon potatoes)
Nice place to have dessert and coffee/tea after dinner. Very romantic atmosphere. The service was right on the mark.

Love this place! The food is amazing, the staff is really nice and their service is pretty fast for such a busy place. I highly recommend this place.my boyfriend and I often choose this restaurant athough bell blvd has many other great places to eat.

Excellent option for Greek food on Bell Boulevard.  Food is delicious and you get ample portions, making it a great value.  Plenty of seating and service is always friendly.  Personal faves are any of the meats in "doner" form (sandwich or platter) as well as the Greek fries.
Food is great. I came for a late lunch so not busy nor loud. But not surprising at 3pm.

One of the best Greek places in Northern Queens. Friendly staff, great food and prompt service.  The best seat in the house is all the way in the back. Upfront is where they cook and can get too hot. And in the winter, the door is constantly being opened up for people coming in, which can get too cold.

This amazing Greek food is second only to the incredible food I had in Greece. I get the moussaka every time (almost like a Greek shepherd's pie) and any appetizer is so worth it. Also love the authentic Greek coffee and nice patio. I can't come to Queens without coming here.

I love coming to Avli! It is great for big groups, especially since my friends and I love to try different things.  We usually get a ton of different plates and share them, and the prices are very affordable.  My friend who is Greek also …

Amazing.  I've been coming here a few times now and true the service is a bit slow but WHO CARES?!?! the food beat it all.  Tried different stuff all the time (tzatziki is a must) and it has always been delicious.

Best Greek food! I usually order the Gyro platter which comes with lemon soup or Greek salad and fries. The pita bread is always fresh and the tzatziki sauce that comes with it is awesome. The skirt steak is also really good and juicy. The …
delicious salads

I have been here twice since April of last year, it is absolutely fantastic! Excellent service!!!! Fantastic setting, and even better food! Try the lemon chicken soup, as well as the gyros! I DEFINITELY recommend coming here if you are in the area!!!!

It's all about the Tzatziki.  Hands down the best I've had anywhere, and well, if you put it on anything you're eating, that too will be the best you've had anywhere.  I wish the gyro wasn't so good, this way I'd try another meal of the menu, but I'm hooked.  I've tried the roasted vegetables and the lemon potatoes too, both great.
